cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as word and sentence embeddings, and similarity estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes supervised models that leverage these representations for prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of contextualized embeddings such as ELMo and BERT suggests the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a bidirectional LSTM, which is a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper addresses benchmark datasets, which suggests the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
